  // Finding #12 — set to workflowInstanceId only for LIVE multinode sessions; a partial
  // UNIQUE index (see migration) enforces at most one live multinode session per instance.
  // Non-multinode sessions leave this null (nulls don't collide); the partial index drops the
  // row once the session reaches a terminal state (completed/approved/failed/abandoned), so a
  // re-run starts clean.
